"Somewhere, in a sparsely populated galaxy, there is a planet like any other. The creatures of this world have four limbs. The two lower limbs enable them to move forward and backward, and the two upper limbs enable them to kill"
This quote is from experimental sci-fi animation masterpiece called ‘Fantastic Planet’ directed by Rène Laloux and based on Stefan's Wul novel. It isn't hard to guess whom this quote is referring to as 'the creatures' with four 'limbs'. It's also easy to understand that Syro 'Drague' Knit is a loving tribute to this very movie. This magnificent blue garment has a loose cropped fit and it is topped with a 3D visualization of the main character inhabiting "Fantastic Planet", called "Drague" as the sweater does.
The meaning of the 'Drague' Knit is based on film's narrative allegory about animal rights and human rights, as well as racism — problems that remain extremely relevant to this day.

Meta Sweatshirt is a look at digital clothing through the internet and self-expression. The sweatshirt touches on the topic of Internet slander. It shows a subway map that doesn't exist. Although there is an official website of this metro in the city of Barnaul, which tourists and even the townspeople of the city of Barnaul believe in. It really looks very realistic and may well compete with the website of the existing metro. Such the website is far from the only fake subway website on the Internet. Fake information on the Internet is a huge problem of the 21st century that needs to be addressed. This Meta Sweatshirt reminds us that you don't always have to believe what is written on the Internet

The dress has a flounce structure arching around the body from the front neck towards the back, following the curved vertical panels. The construction and inspirations are eclectic, coming from different types of garments such as bodycon dress, evening gown, and even elements from active wear in the form of ribbed inserts and cut out racer back detail. When creating this design I was exploring my interest in merging seemingly opposing elements into a refined whole, while creating a unique piece for a virtual wardrobe.

Flared jeans with a combination of different textures: laser printed denim and shiny satin with a camo-inspired digital print. The pants have iridescent ribbed flounces inserted in leg panels. The legs are cut into curved vertical panels, based on various inspirations such as anatomic shapes, active- and shape-wear, denim wear, even cowboy trousers. The construction and inspirations are eclectic, coming from different types of trousers, as I am interested in merging seemingly opposing elements into a refined whole. When creating this design I was interested in exploring the trouser as a functional garment (taking inspiration for various types of 'leg wear'). Since this is a piece for a digital wardrobe I wanted to create something that draws details from the real world, but in a digital world would gain a different significance, as the functionality aspect is ruled out.

I drew inspiration from Vivienne Westwood bridal wear and alexander McQueen's spring 2012 lace masks.

A bomber jacket with a combination of different textures: laser printed denim and shiny satin with a camo-inspired digital print. The jacket has an iridescent rib collar in the front that follows along the sleeves as a flounce structure. I am interested in merging seemingly opposing elements into a refined whole and enjoy exploring creative pattern transformations. When creating this design I was exploring the functionality and history of the bomber jacket (also named as flight jacket, therefor the ribbed flounces suggesting the idea of wings) as a functional clothing piece in aviation - given the current global context of war. While the colors and textures are completely opposing to the idea of army clothing: bright colors, iridescent, shiny textures.
Future tuxedo

A black leather dress with a boning top, and a chiffon detail on the shoulders. Gives the vibes of a girl go-getter, a girl who knows what she wants and she's not afraid to take it. A mafia girl-boss.
Particles, like pollen, are flying around the body. The iridescence effect gives freshness to the classic silhouette of this dress.
Like a lively, bubbly, and mysterious aquatic creature roaming in the deep ocean, the indigo glow is flowing all over the veins with the breath.

The source of inspiration when designing the skirt was the structural geometry of the natural form - volcanic glass. The draperies of the skirt repeat the outlines of the obsidian shape, and the matte and glossy elements imitate the textures of natural stone.

The Matrix dress is about the technologies. Unusual materials and elements make it possible to delve into technology and "feel" the texture of clothing, as well as to get closer to the future. This dress is available in two colors.

The down jacket was created as a part of collection "Planet Parade". Mars is closely tied to the war in mass culture. This is why the look was inspired by Japanese traditional armor, Evangelion mechas and many other militaristic symbols.

node.item_name: trendy wide leg jeans with suspenders
node.description: I like to learn new fashion trends and try to use everything new and interesting in my work. The combination of a short top and tight short shorts with rough wide irregularly shaped jeans seemed very interesting to me.

The main idea is a creation of second skin for the soul - really passionate and full of life. Digital fashion let us fantasize about different shapes of our body and emotions that are raging inside. My work is an expression of inner fire.
Windbreaker - down jacket for any weather. Summer in the morning and winter in the evening. You never know what will happen in your life during the day.
Therapeutic soft light and straight flare fabric pants, with messy dark knotted bubble stiff top. Yin and Yang. Soft and Strong.

This cape is a so far only digital garment that was inspired by ZeroWaste. Zero Waste is a method to completely consume the material without leaving any excess. Although regarding sustainability it‘s not the non plus ultra, but one brick in the sustainable philosophy. This cape means protection, modern construction, utility, transformation and flexibilty. The fit is based on principles of dressmaking, high quality, trendresearch and perfection in tailoring. Colour: Off-black, Enye-Tech-Green, Hyper-lilac Digital material: Raw-denim, Heavy grain leather, Cotton stretch material Sizes: Available in every size

The design of garments was built on the idea of healing sounds. The Chladni plates (the visualization of sound vibrations) provide a therapeutic effect on the human body. The prints for the collection refer to images of the plate's surface and motion between various frequency values. Sooner or later, fashion tech specialists will create "healing garments" for daily use to make people calm down during anxiety, but now it's just a fantasy of the future of techwear.
A dress in case you feel radiant, liquid and slightly toxic

The pale lagoon green color and the delicate folds of the Dew Dress draw inspiration from the serene image of morning dew. The dress encapsulates both the freshness of dawn and the intricate curves of dew droplets.
I was inspired by extraterrestrial life forms and I created something alien and fantastic. This item is from completely different planet.

FASHION&TECH IN A FANTASTIC OUTFIT. This is a look all about connections and information encripted in this amazing texture. Do you want to find it out? Wear it! Connect with it! Share your history and let this information to be saved and registered between materials and colors.
node.auth_choosen_name: FANTASTIC 3D FASHION BY GIOVANNA MARÇALLO THEREZA

node.description: Betta Fish is a dress inspired by the colors, pleated fins, and flowy body of the Betta fish. I added my signature touch, the gold details, to add a fancy element to the dress.

Showing clothes as an independent object is always important to me as an artist. Bright color, gradient, complex design tell more things about hard character. The complex form simultaneously protects, but also calls for action.

Genesis and Genetics are two words for which the dress's name was born. We are living in an era where human beings need to re-connect with their beginning, with nature, and feel it as part of their DNA if they want to continue living in this world. The dress represents this new form of life, a balanced fusion of organic shapes and different materials (especially organic silk) layering and overlapping in harmony. The colors contrast in order to represent the never-ending cycle of life and passing of time, vibrant and muted, new and old, origins and tradition in balance with new ways and contemporary visions.

The idea behind this garment was to create something that can mix the simplicity of a bomber jacket with a complex and appealing design. The colors I have chosen have the purpose to recall hot places in contrast to the classic use of a bomber jacket to fight the cold. The design aims to stimulate the imagination of the wearer giving him total control over what he sees in the shapes of the jacket. I choose to develop this garment in 3D because realize it in real live could be very expensive but I still wanted to evaluate the impact of such design on the public.

Do you want a sweet carrot?
From: A.D.A. (digital atelier)
Digital adult sleepers overalls with print: "pacifier" can back to childrenhood and present funny mood
A green-pink dress with a puffy hem that allows you not to languish in the summer, and if it gets colder, you can even sit on the cold steps.

I was inspired by the beauty of metal corrosion, incredible overflows of rust and peeling paint in places. To create the shape of the dress, I used the blots I drew and then experimented with textures in Photoshop

A lot of my designs are focused on bringing the digital and the natural together. In this case I my starting point was in the ethereal beauty of the shadows of plants in the wind. I found it fascinating how it contrasts with the way we view digital images, where we are able to see digital images through the light our screens emit, we can see these projections of plants by the absence of that light. The garments themselves are transparent in a purposefully artificial way to let the natural but digitised light shine from withing them.
Purplle crystal
dress was inspired by organic shapes
This is my interpretation of a mermaid costume inspired by the shapes of the sea wave and the incredible colors of the ocean depths.

This dress is included in the collection "Midsummer night". Cool summer nights beckon with the sweet scent of mattiola in the garden, where the dew shimmers on the cobwebs, and the moon accompanies you on a midnight romantic date with him...
The garment was developed from existing garments with a view to recycling a crochet cloth with a classic military padding. Genderless, if you like it, you can wear it.

ZERO is an edgy but casual spin on puffer-wear that draws Inspiration from retro anime and space suits; an iridescent and hydrophobic fit for the modern introvert. Pants have in-built programmable LED displays. You can't drown in this drip.

Conceived from unwearable materials, Eter explores the infinite possibilities of the virtual and creates new digital wear. This garment is a two layered tank top: a translucent glassy top covered in hard melting metal, creating a balance between exploring fantasies through clothing and desirable items that we would love to have in real life.
This is the digital version of our John Jacket which we were inspired by the music and social position of the legendary John Lennon. it's a mix of biker jackets and hippie ponchos

Live fast and overthink. Have you ever been out and about feeling luscious and suddenly the dread for the future knocked in? This spicy, coquettish dress is here to ask everyone. The answer is always: enjoy the moment.
Heavy chest. Anxiety. What comes next. Perfect pants.
A velvet off-shoulder black dress with a slit for when the hot girl is widowed in her 30s. Sad yet sophisticated and elegant.

This dress was inspired by the sunset, it's made in a gradient fabric that goes between orange and purple. the dress has five layers of accordion pleats that flare out at the end to reach that touch of gold like the sunset sky has these subtle sunrays.

The realization has come that you have failed to protect yourself from the influence of white noise (the opinions of others, the media, the daily routine, groundhog day, the noise of cars and the noise of human life, the monotonous cycle).
White noise overrides the voice of my inner self. This noise makes it hard to hear and understand yourself.
Nastro dress is an elegant and essential dress. It wraps the shape of the body enhancing harmonious lines. The material is iridescent and enameled, enveloping you like an ancient goddess.

I was born in a small village inside the hills, surrounded of green. The ispiration for Coraline coat is born from here, I mixed the mood from my grandma's old photographs with every shades of green that I see around me every day.

All products were created with the support of the new digital atelier A.D.A. (Alkali Digital Atelier) The first costume "Pieces" is created for people, who wants to try clothes that cannot be in realitys are created for any gender and they can be worn separately.
Digital Dress [Sakura (new beginnings) + iPhone (accessibility to tech) + Eyes (navigating warnings)] = From the Dev桜ce

The Radiance dress is inspired by the role of women in today's world. And metaphorically all the roles are reflected in this attire. The armor symbolizes the function of protecting the family, children and oneself. Luminous side elements with a train refer to the social component, where they achieve success, create new projects and leave a significant mark on history. An animated twinkling centerpiece front and back shows how women fill the world with beauty and brilliance, and how they change the world around them.
Spacial Jumper with iridiscent and translucent materials

This dress is simple from a pattern-making point of view but has the twist of lots of ostrich feathers attatched to the skirt. This and the colours chosen make the wearer stand out from the mass for sure!
Flowy yet elegant go-to staple for a chic-classic and fierce aesthetic.
The hot and the cold. The natural and the mystical. Dreamy.
A playful oversized digital puffer jacket with the ability to express love with an animated heart in AR.
This inflatable dress was created as a part of collection "Planet Parade". In Roman mythology Venus is a goddess of love and beauty. This is why the piece of garment has a very mild feminine look.

Inspired by the feelings, Thoughts and conversations that astronauts have throughout their journeys, Thinking that somehow all these stay inside the ship, keeping their joys, discoveries and uncertainties. This design reflects all the moments and experiences they lived through and makes us remember everything they have achieved.

The NeoDIABLO piece is the result of the junction of references that border the Y2K aesthetic with a lifestile of those who love and consume content aimed at TRASH terror. The futuristic with the nostalgic resulted in a jacket that represents this union of references.

Olska Green (founder of the Ecoolska brand and fashion designer) was inspired by biodiversity of wonderful underwater world. The beauty of nature is the best source of inspiration. Algae plays a significant and integral role in the marine ecosystem. It is very important for balancing marine ecosystems and plays a role in thwarting climate change. You can feel like a mermaid from a fairy tale if you virtually try on this flowing elegant digital dress.

I am looking for inspiration in the real world and I want to reflect its beauty in the virtual world. I wanted to create an unusual dress design and complement it with an interesting texture. I hope I managed to get your attention. thanks!
